---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Egypt Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/egypt/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Jordan for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/jordan' },
  { title: 'Tunisia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/tunisia' },
  { title: 'Morocco for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/morocco' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'egyptFit', header: 'Egypt Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'EGP 12,000-17,000/mo', egyptFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'EGP 14,000-20,000/mo', egyptFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'EGP 11,000-16,000/mo', egyptFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'EGP 10,000-14,500/mo', egyptFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Egyptian Local', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: 'EGP 2,000-6,000/mo', egyptFit: 'Basic Option' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'EGP 11,000-17,000', annual: 'EGP 132,000-204,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'EGP 15,000-23,000', annual: 'EGP 180,000-276,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'EGP 20,000-30,000', annual: 'EGP 240,000-360,000' },
  { category: 'Egyptian Private Hospital', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: 'EGP 500-1,500/visit' },
  { category: 'Egyptian Public', monthly: 'Free/nominal', annual: 'Limited quality' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Egypt 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Egypt. Pyramids, Nile cruises, extremely affordable living, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Egypt"
  subheadline="Egypt offers ancient wonders, Nile Valley magic, Red Sea beaches, and extremely affordable living—a unique retirement destination for adventurous budget-conscious seniors."
  heroImage="/images/countries/egypt-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Egypt</h2>
  <p>
    Egypt offers unmatched ancient history, Nile Valley culture, Red Sea diving, and extremely affordable living. The Egyptian pound devaluation has made costs remarkably low for foreign pension holders. Winter climate is excellent—warm and sunny when Europe freezes.
  </p>

  <p>
    Cairo provides mega-city living near pyramids with best healthcare. Luxor offers Nile Valley immersion with temples at doorstep. Red Sea coast (Hurghada, El Gouna, Sharm el-Sheikh) attracts beach/diving retirees. Alexandria provides Mediterranean charm. Each region offers distinct Egyptian experience.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good private in Cairo; limited elsewhere</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Arabic; English in tourist areas</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> EGP 20,000-50,000/month (~$400-1,000); extremely low</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Desert; hot summers, warm winters</li>
      <li><strong>History:</strong> Pyramids, Luxor, Valley of Kings at doorstep</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Ancient wonder; bustling; chaotic; affordable</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Egypt's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Egypt has good private healthcare concentrated in Cairo—As-Salam International Hospital, Dar Al Fouad, and major private hospitals provide quality care. Red Sea resort areas have adequate clinics. Outside Cairo and tourist areas, quality drops significantly.
  </p>

  <p>
    Public healthcare exists but is overcrowded and underfunded—not recommended for expats. For complex care, evacuation to Europe or Gulf states may be needed. International insurance with evacuation coverage is essential for seniors outside Cairo.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Cairo-Centric Quality</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Quality healthcare is concentrated in Cairo. If retiring to Luxor, Red Sea, or other areas, plan for Cairo travel for serious care or evacuation. Private hospitals in Cairo are adequate for most senior needs. Complex cases may need evacuation to Dubai or Europe.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Egypt offers accessible options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa + Extensions</h3>
  <p>
    Single-entry visa on arrival (most nationalities). 30 days, extendable to 6 months. Some retirees use repeated tourist visas while exploring Egypt.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For longer stays—requires proof of income, accommodation, health insurance. Process is bureaucratic. Apply through Interior Ministry. Valid 1 year, renewable.
  </p>

  <h3>Property Ownership</h3>
  <p>
    Owning property supports residence applications. Egypt allows foreign property ownership in most areas (some restrictions in Sinai). Property is very affordable by international standards.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Egypt:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence permit:</strong> Health insurance typically required</li>
    <li><strong>Practical need:</strong> Private coverage essential (public limited)</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Essential for locations outside Cairo</li>
    <li><strong>Cairo hospitals:</strong> Ensure coverage at major private facilities</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Egypt</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for Egypt seniors. Local insurers have age limits and coverage gaps. Ensure plan covers: Cairo private hospitals, evacuation to Dubai/Europe, and emergency repatriation. Outside Cairo, evacuation coverage is critical.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Egypt, international coverage with evacuation is essential:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Egypt</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good MENA network, evacuation included</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Now Health:</strong> Middle East expertise, regional knowledge</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive regional pricing</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with evacuation essential for Egypt retirement.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Egypt are moderate given the need for international coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Egyptian private care is cheap; high deductible for serious issues</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash routine:</strong> Private consultations EGP 500-1,000; very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Cairo base:</strong> Best healthcare access if you need regular care</li>
    <li><strong>Regional coverage:</strong> MENA + Europe focused rather than worldwide</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: British Egyptophile, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £1,400/month pension. Lifelong dream to live near pyramids.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Residence permit. Cigna Global with UK coverage. Lives in Giza; uses Dar Al Fouad Hospital.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~EGP 14,000/month (~£290). Ancient wonders at doorstep on modest pension.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: German Diver Couple, Both 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Combined pension €2,200/month. Retiring to El Gouna (Red Sea).</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for both with evacuation. Uses El Gouna clinic + Cairo for serious needs.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~EGP 35,000/month combined (~€720). Red Sea diving paradise; Cairo healthcare accessible.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: American History Lover, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,800/month pension. Moving to Luxor for temples and Nile life.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Now Health with evacuation coverage. Uses local clinics; Cairo for specialists.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Now Health ~EGP 12,000/month (~$250). Valley of Kings at doorstep; excellent value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Egypt safe for retirees?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Tourist areas are generally safe—heavily policed since terrorism concerns. Cairo is chaotic but not dangerous with standard precautions. Sinai has travel restrictions. Avoid political gatherings. Most expat retirees in tourist areas and expat communities live comfortably.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How affordable is Egypt really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Extremely affordable—pound devaluation means Western pensions go very far. Quality apartments $200-400/month. Full meal at good restaurant $5-10. Domestic staff affordable. $1,000-1,500/month supports comfortable lifestyle. One of the world's most affordable retirement destinations.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's daily life like in Egypt?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Chaotic, vibrant, and unique. Traffic is intense. Bureaucracy is frustrating. But culture is rich, people are welcoming, history is everywhere. Many find it energizing; some find it exhausting. Test with extended visit before committing. Not for everyone but unforgettable for those who embrace it.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I get by with English?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        In tourist areas (hotels, major sites, expat communities)—yes. Everyday life (markets, taxis, bureaucracy)—Arabic helps enormously. Healthcare in private Cairo hospitals usually has English-speaking staff. Learning Arabic basics improves life significantly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with evacuation coverage essential for Egypt.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/now-health" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Now Health Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Egyptian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
